Mountain in Spring by Valentin Sidorov Photo: Courtesy of NAMCA new exhibition featuring paintings and sculptures from Russian artists Valentin Sidorov and Andrey Kovalchuk kicked off at National Art Museum of China (NAMC) on Sunday. According to exhibition curator Wu Weishan, viewers can feel Sidorov's love and nostalgia for his hometown through his paintings, while Kovalchuk brings his thoughts into the world through his sculptures. The exhibition features a total of 24 paintings and 34 sculptures. Additionally, Sidorov has donated five paintings to the museum, while Kovalchuk has donated seven sculptures. The exhibition is set to run until August 11.  
